---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About tool.news — Developer Tool Comparison & Lock-in Analysis"
  description="tool.news is an open-source, automatically updated catalog of 1,700+ developer tools. Unique metrics: Lock-in Score, Migration Difficulty, Pricing Transparency. Built by HeyLabs."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
      About tool.news
    </h1>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        tool.news is an automatic catalog of <strong>1,700+ developer tools</strong>, updated every
        <strong>6 hours</strong>. Our goal is to give developers transparent, comparable data so they
        can pick the right tool without hours of research.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white pt-4">What makes us different</h2>

      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li>
          <strong>Lock-in Score</strong> — a 0-5 rating of how difficult it is to leave a tool,
          covering data portability, API compatibility, and proprietary formats.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Migration Difficulty</strong> — an honest assessment of the effort required to
          switch from one tool to another.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Pricing Transparency</strong> — we surface free tiers, entry prices, billing
          complexity, and whether pricing is publicly available.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white pt-4">How it's built</h2>

      <p>
        The site is built with <strong>Astro</strong> and hosted on <strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong>.
        Data is sourced from the <strong>GitHub API</strong>, <strong>npm</strong>, and
        <strong>Hacker News</strong>, then processed into structured JSON files that feed the catalog.
      </p>

      <p class="rounded-lg bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 p-4 text-sm font-medium">
        $0/month infrastructure — static generation + edge hosting keeps costs at zero.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
